The paper is focused on developing reasoning tools for dependency quantified Boolean formulas (DQBF), which is a subfield of logic and automated reasoning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of automated testing and debugging techniques, which are common in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses pre- and in-processing techniques, which are relevant to the subfield of data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper mentions the extension of DQBF from quantified Boolean formulas (QBF), which is a subfield of programming languages (cs.PL).
